description:
Angelina (she/her/hers) is a Senior Product Manager (PM) at Amazon where she drives global product features and roadmap prioritization for digital video games. She owns the domain/roadmap across seven marketplaces for customer discovery which includes the customer shopping journey from search, product detail page, and checkout. Angelina transitioned into product management in 2017 and has been passionate about not only learning and building inclusive products, but also increasing the knowledge and representation of Black, Indigenous, and people of color (BIPOC) in product management.

In addition to her PM role, she is the President of the Black Employee Network (BEN), an Employee Resource Group (ERG) at Amazon. She focuses on being an advocate for inclusion and diversity, driving different initiatives and programs internally/externally, advising Amazonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s senior leaders, and growing a community inside and outside of Amazon. She co-founded several initiatives at Amazon including BEN Startup Week, a weeighlight and support Black entrepreneurs, and the Black Excellence Gala, a scholarship event for organizations supporting underrepresented youth in STEM.

Angelina is a freelance instructor, adjunct professor at the University of Arkansas, speaker, and business and corporate diversity consultant. In 2019 she started her blog to provide insight into a career in product management.

description:
Entrepreneur and aspiring product manager.

As a first-generation Asian American, I've seen the struggles my parents went through to give a better life to my sister, brother, and me. They raised me up to never be afraid of hard work and be laser-focused on my dreams and goals. Oh boy, do I have many. Some of them are  

1. Giving my parents the lifestyle they thought can't become a reality
2. Empowering others with the mindset and resources to achieve dreams 
3. Creating a global impact in causes I care about (Breast Cancer Research, Women in Tech, etc.)

I knew those can't be realized through just working a job my whole life, so I chose to build and scale businesses under the guidance of successful entrepreneurs on the side.

Looking forward to connecting with other like-minded individuals! Happy to see if I could be of help. 


Interests: 
- Having heart to heart convos about life
- Playing sports (badminton, basketball, taekwondo, etc.)
- Personal development
- Jamming to music (mainly pop, kpop, cpop)

During my time at Google, I've had the great opportunity to work in our two core businesses: Search & Search Ads. Within these groups, I've been even more fortunate to lead projects that are top-level organizational priorities due to their impact and scale, providing unique opportunities to learn and grow in highly visible and cross-functional environments.

In Search Ads, I led the effort to optimize and evolve the user interface of Google Search on mobile. As the lead PM, I provided strategic direction to a team of 20+ engineers, designers, quantitative analysts, and researchers to brainstorm, experiment, and launch whole-page redesigns that improved the user experience of Search while also driving value to advertisers. These efforts drove multi-billion dollar impact to Google revenue and were launched toï¿½ï¿½all mobile users of Search, affecting hundreds of millions of people per day.ï¿½ï¿½

Today, I'm a product manager complete, the product that helps users complete their queries to Search across all platforms (mobile web, desktop, and the Google Search apps). Since this product sits at the very top of the funnel, improvements our team makes have the potential to significantly impact top-level Search metrics and usership, once again making this area a top-level strategic priority for Google. 

I love to play golf, drink cold brew coffee, explore new cities and foods, and recently have been trying my hand at cooking! I'm originally from Chicago, Illinois but now reside in San Francisco, California.

jobDescription2:
In November 2014, Amazon announced Alexa alongside Echo. Alexa was inspired by the computer voice and conversational system on board the star ship Enterprise in science fiction TV series and movies, beginning with Star Trek TOS and Star Trek TNG. The name Alexa was chosen due to the fact that it has a hard consonant with the X and therefore could be recognized with higher precision. The name is also claimed to be reminiscent of the Library of Alexandria.

Alexa is an intelligent personal assistant developed by Amazon, made popular by the Amazon Echo and the Amazon Echo Dot devices developed by Amazon Lab126. It is capable of voice interaction, music playback, making to-do lists, setting alarms, streaming podcasts, playing audio books, and providing weather, traffic, and other real time information, such as news. Alexa can also control several smart devices using itself as a home automation system.
